<subSubSection id="D6B9258EC6E2FF132A9C9E1B33C07893" pageId="150" pageNumber="151" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9E1C7605C6E2FF132A9C9E1B33C07893" blockId="150.[151,1437,329,498]" pageId="150" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C6E2FF132A9C9E1B32037803" bold="true" box="[151,273,329,354]" pageId="150" pageNumber="151">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Easily distinguished from similar known congeners (
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C6E2FF1329749E1830E57803" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[895,1015,329,354]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Carapoia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="150" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="djavani">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C6E2FF1329749E1830E57803" box="[895,1015,329,354]" italics="true" pageId="150" pageNumber="151">C. djavani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C6E2FF132E039E1837787803" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1032,1130,329,354]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Carapoia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="150" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agilis">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C6E2FF132E039E1837787803" box="[1032,1130,329,354]" italics="true" pageId="150" pageNumber="151">C. agilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by shape of procursus in dorsal view (small prolateral branch at tip; 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C6E2FF1328729E3F31C878E7" box="[633,730,365,390]" captionStart="FIGURES677–682" captionStartId="151.[151,264,1766,1788]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@151.[151,1436,193,1745]" captionTargetPageId="151" captionText="FIGURES677–682. Carapoia exigua sp. n. (♂: ZFMK Ar 19291; ♀: UFMG 21557).677–678.Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 679. Left procursus, dorsal view. 680. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 681. Epigynum, ventral view. 682. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines:0.3 (677–678), 0.2 (679–682)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202683/files/figure.png" pageId="150" pageNumber="151">Fig. 679</figureCitation>
), by arrangement of frontal cheliceral apophyses (
<figureCitation id="06986A80C6E2FF132F009E3F367F78E7" box="[1291,1389,365,390]" captionStart="FIGURES677–682" captionStartId="151.[151,264,1766,1788]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@151.[151,1436,193,1745]" captionTargetPageId="151" captionText="FIGURES677–682. Carapoia exigua sp. n. (♂: ZFMK Ar 19291; ♀: UFMG 21557).677–678.Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 679. Left procursus, dorsal view. 680. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 681. Epigynum, ventral view. 682. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines:0.3 (677–678), 0.2 (679–682)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202683/files/figure.png" pageId="150" pageNumber="151">Fig. 680</figureCitation>
), by shape of epigynum (anterior plate trapezoidal, posterior margin projecting medially; 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C6E2FF132E7C9EC337CE78CB" box="[1143,1244,401,426]" captionStart="FIGURES677–682" captionStartId="151.[151,264,1766,1788]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@151.[151,1436,193,1745]" captionTargetPageId="151" captionText="FIGURES677–682. Carapoia exigua sp. n. (♂: ZFMK Ar 19291; ♀: UFMG 21557).677–678.Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 679. Left procursus, dorsal view. 680. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 681. Epigynum, ventral view. 682. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines:0.3 (677–678), 0.2 (679–682)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202683/files/figure.png" pageId="150" pageNumber="151">Fig. 681</figureCitation>
), and by female internal genitalia (distinctively shaped pore-plates, diverging sclerites between anterior and posterior plates; 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C6E2FF132F7B9EE733D47893" captionStart="FIGURES677–682" captionStartId="151.[151,264,1766,1788]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@151.[151,1436,193,1745]" captionTargetPageId="151" captionText="FIGURES677–682. Carapoia exigua sp. n. (♂: ZFMK Ar 19291; ♀: UFMG 21557).677–678.Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 679. Left procursus, dorsal view. 680. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 681. Epigynum, ventral view. 682. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines:0.3 (677–678), 0.2 (679–682)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202683/files/figure.png" pageId="150" pageNumber="151">Fig. 682</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
