<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C6E3FF12282F99B4314F7F9D" bold="true" box="[548,605,1766,1788]" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(♂: ZFMK Ar 19291; ♀: UFMG 21557). 677–678. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 679. Left procursus, dorsal view. 680. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 681. Epigynum, ventral view. 682. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view. Scale lines: 0.3 (677–678), 0.2 (679–682).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="D6B9258EC6E3FF122ACC982D32167EDD" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="9E1C7605C6E3FF122ACC982D32167EDD" blockId="151.[151,1436,1919,2016]" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C6E3FF122ACC982D325C7EF9" bold="true" box="[199,334,1919,1944]" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the small size of this species (Latin 
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C6E3FF122E6498D336367EF9" box="[1135,1316,1921,1944]" italics="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">
exiguus, 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C6E3FF122ED298D336367EF9" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1241,1316,1921,1944]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Carapoia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exigua">exigua</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
= small); adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
